The transformation efficiency of G-AgarTrap varied significantly with the use of
different
Agrobacterium
strains; the strains yielding the highest and lowest efficiencies
were EHA101 and MP90, respectively. In a previous study using tomato (
Solanum
lycopersicum
), it was suggested that differences in transformation efficiency using
different
Agrobacterium
strains was caused by variations in the plant tissue mortality
which might also be the case in the present study. Additionally, for many methods using
